Cognition - Immediate recall

1 Description of DataSchema variable

The description of harmonised variable is the following:

  • Short name: cog_imm
  • Variable label: Cognition - immediate recall
  • Variable description: Immediate recall of common nouns from a list. Variable dichotomised by first quartil with value 0 and higher with value 1.
  • Domain: Health status and functional limitations
  • Value type: categorical
  • Category coding:

2.1.1.2 Harmonisation algorithm

To compute the harmonize variable cog_imm_c from the study-specific variable the missing values have to be recoded as follows:

  • -9 Refusal into 997
  • -8 Don't know into 998
  • -1 Not applicable into 996
  • NA into 999

To compute the harmonized variable cog_imm from cog_imm_c it has to be recoded as follows:

  • cog_imm_c <=25% into 0
  • cog_imm_c >25% into 1

R script

## cog_imm_c
ELSA_ds_w1 <- tibble(id = ELSA_w1_cog_imm$id)
ELSA_ds_w1$cog_imm_c <- car::recode(ELSA_w1_cog_imm$cflisen, "-9 = 997; -8 = 998; -1 = 996")


## cog_imm
Q <- quantile(car::recode(ELSA_ds_w1$cog_imm_c, "999=NA;997=NA;998=NA;996=NA"), 
    probs = 1/4, na.rm = TRUE, names = FALSE)

ELSA_ds_w1$cog_imm <- car::recode(ELSA_ds_w1[[2]], "0:Q=0; (Q+1):10=1")
